## ASYNC/AWAIT RULES (Python)

### When to Use Async:
- ✅ Database queries (async SQLAlchemy)
- ✅ External API calls
- ✅ File I/O
- ✅ Redis operations
- ✅ WebSocket connections

### When NOT to Use Async:
- ❌ Pure computation (CPU-bound)
- ❌ Wasm execution (already non-blocking)
- ❌ Simple variable assignments

### Pattern:
```python
# ✅ GOOD
async def create_battle(user_id: int):
    async with AsyncSession(engine) as session:
        battle = Battle(user_id=user_id)
        session.add(battle)
        await session.commit()
        return battle

# ❌ BAD (blocking call in async function)
async def bad_example():
    result = some_sync_function()  # This blocks event loop!
    return result
```

